Package nl.pim16aap2.animatedarchitecture.core.structures.properties

Class Property<T>

java.lang.Object
nl.pim16aap2.animatedarchitecture.core.structures.properties.Property<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the property.
All Implemented Interfaces:
IKeyed
public final class Property<T> extends Object implements IKeyed
Represents a property of a structure.

Several properties are predefined in this class. For example, the OPEN_STATUS property is used to represent whether a structure is open or closed.

  • Constructor Details

    • Property

      public Property(NamespacedKey namespacedKey, Class<T> type, @Nullable T defaultValue, PropertyAccessLevel propertyAccessLevel, PropertyScope... scopes)
      Creates a new property.
      Parameters:
      namespacedKey - The namespace and key of the property.
      type - The type of the property.
      defaultValue - The default value of the property.

      This is the value that will be used if a structure whose type has this property does not have a value set for this property.

      propertyAccessLevel - The level of access users have to this property.
      scopes - The scopes in which this property is used.

      This is used to prevent side effects of changing the property value. For example, clearing cached values related to the property, such as the animation range when changing the blocks to move.

    • Property

      public Property(String owner, String name, Class<T> type, @Nullable T defaultValue, PropertyAccessLevel propertyAccessLevel, PropertyScope... scopes)
      Creates a new property.
      Parameters:
      owner - The name of the plugin that owns this property. This is used to prevent conflicts between properties between different plugins.

      All properties supplied by this plugin are set to Constants.PLUGIN_NAME.

      Properties from other plugins should use the name of the plugin that owns the property.

      name - The name of the property that is used for serialization.
      type - The type of the property.
      defaultValue - The default value of the property.

      This is the value that will be used if a structure whose type has this property does not have a value set for this property.

      propertyAccessLevel - The level of access users have to this property.
      scopes - The scopes in which this property is used.

      This is used to prevent side effects of changing the property value. For example, clearing cached values related to the property, such as the animation range when changing the blocks to move.
